"Rolf Moulton, the new president and CEO of (ISC)2, doesn't believe that the people who violate computer systems are all bad. “There are very few black and whites, but lots of greys,” he says with a soft New York accent. He doesn't subscribe to the view of a strict division between the dark and good sides. This insightful attitude comes from his early career experiences, in the Department of Investigation of the City of New York. “You come out more human, after working at the Department,” says Moulton."
